data.text:
Homer COBURN was born in March 1894 in Missouri. Parents: William H. COBURN and Sarah Jane APPLEBERRY.

Spouse: Ina Felicia GARR. Ina Felicia GARR and Homer COBURN were married. Children were: Leona Mamie COBURN, Mildred Myrtle COBURN, Mervin COBURN, William H. COBURN.

Hyman T. COBURN was born (date unknown). Parents: Barzilla COBURN and Elizabeth Ann SHARP.James "Jim" COBURN was born (date unknown). Parents: Kenneth "Ken" COBURN and Mary Rachel BONDERER.James Marion COBURN was born on 7 March 1854 in Livingston Co., Missouri. He died on 27 February 1935 at the age of 80 in Chillicothe, Livingston, Missouri. He was buried on 1 March 1935 in Burnside Cemetery, Livingston, Missouri. Parents: Luther COBURN and Elizabeth "Betty" PATTERSON.

Spouse: Ellen BLACKWELL. Ellen BLACKWELL and James Marion COBURN were married on 5 March 1876 in Livingston Co., Missouri. Children were: Addie B. COBURN, Edna Jane COBURN, Jesse Adron COBURN.

Jesse Adron COBURN was born on 24 December 1884 in Avalon, Livingston, Missouri. He died on 15 March 1971 at the age of 86 in Chillicothe Hospital, Livingston, Missouri. He was buried on 17 March 1971 in Resthaven Memorial Gardens, Livingston, Missouri. Parents: James Marion COBURN and Ellen BLACKWELL.

Spouse: Charlotte Mable "Lottie" WILLIAMS. Charlotte Mable "Lottie" WILLIAMS and Jesse Adron COBURN were married on 17 February 1910 in Avalon, Livingston, Missouri. The bride was of Avalon, the groom of Bedford. Children were: Buel Earl COBURN, Edna Pearl COBURN.

Jewell Linnius COBURN was born on 12 June 1898 in Avalon, Livingston, Missouri. He died on 26 May 1935 at the age of 36 in Chillicothe, Livingston, Missouri. He was buried on 28 May 1935 in Plainview Cemetery, Livingston, Missouri. Parents: William H. COBURN and Sarah Jane APPLEBERRY.

Spouse: Gertrude Ethyl SCOVILLE. Gertrude Ethyl SCOVILLE and Jewell Linnius COBURN were married on 9 April 1919 in Chula, Livingston, Missouri. The bride was of Chula, the groom of Trenton. Children were: Kenneth "Ken" COBURN, Maxine Everett "Max" COBURN, Bette Mae COBURN, William Henry COBURN.

Jim Estella COBURN was born on 12 February 1894 in Livingston Co., Missouri. She died on 10 March 1922 at the age of 28 in Chillicothe, Livingston, Missouri. She was buried on 12 March 1922 in Edgewood Cemetery, Livingston, Missouri. She never married. Parents: Alonzo C. "Lon" COBURN and Caroline Arnold "Carrie" KNOTTS.Judith Kae COBURN was born (date unknown). Parents: Kenneth "Ken" COBURN and Mary Rachel BONDERER.

Spouse: Joseph Raymond KINSELLA. Judith Kae COBURN and Joseph Raymond KINSELLA were married on 1 June 1963 in Chillicothe, Livingston, Missouri. The bride was of Wheeling, the groom of Chillicothe. Children were: David KINSELLA, Dan KINSELLA, Jeff KINSELLA.

Kenneth "Ken" COBURN was born on 23 December 1919 in Jackson Twp., Grundy, Missouri. He died on 24 October 2000 at the age of 80 in Wheeling, Livingston, Missouri. He was buried on 27 October 2000 in St. Columban Cemetery, Livingston, Missouri. A gravestone is found in Leopolis Cemetery. He was a school bus driver in the Wheeling school district for 17 years.

Parents: Jewell Linnius COBURN and Gertrude Ethyl SCOVILLE.

Spouse: Mary Rachel BONDERER. Mary Rachel BONDERER and Kenneth "Ken" COBURN were married on 2 March 1944 in Chillicothe, Livingston, Missouri. The groom was of Wheeling, Missouri. Children were: James "Jim" COBURN, Judith Kae COBURN.

Leona Mamie COBURN was born on 9 April 1918 in Chula, Livingston, Missouri. She died on 27 May 1996 at the age of 78 in Napa Co., California. She was buried in Napa Co., California. Parents: Homer COBURN and Ina Felicia GARR.

Spouse: Elliott David HAMON. Leona Mamie COBURN and Elliott David HAMON were married on 15 October 1939. Children were: Carol HAMON, Larry HAMON.

Luther COBURN was born in Ohio.

Spouse: Elizabeth "Betty" PATTERSON. Elizabeth "Betty" PATTERSON and Luther COBURN were married on 27 January 1849 in Grand River Twp., Livingston, Missouri. Children were: James Marion COBURN, William H. COBURN.

Luther B. COBURN was born on 7 April 1827 in Ohio. He died on 16 February 1866 at the age of 38 in Livingston Co., Missouri. He was buried in Burnside Cemetery, Livingston, Missouri. He was a Civil War veteran.

Spouse: Masania NEWSON. Masania NEWSON and Luther B. COBURN were married. Children were: Alonzo C. "Lon" COBURN.

Maxine Everett "Max" COBURN was born on 6 June 1921. He died on 22 April 1983 at the age of 61 in Chillicothe, Livingston, Missouri. His widow's obit says he died 21 Apr 1983, conflicting with the reported gravestone inscription. He was buried in Wheeling Cemetery, Livingston, Missouri. Parents: Jewell Linnius COBURN and Gertrude Ethyl SCOVILLE.

Spouse: Beulah Pearl WARREN. Beulah Pearl WARREN and Maxine Everett "Max" COBURN were married on 9 October 1943. Children were: Gary Lee COBURN, Ronald Allen COBURN.

Mervin COBURN was born about 1926 in Missouri. Parents: Homer COBURN and Ina Felicia GARR.Mildred Myrtle COBURN was born in January 1920 in Fairview Twp, , Caldwell, Missouri. Parents: Homer COBURN and Ina Felicia GARR.Ronald Allen COBURN was born (date unknown). Parents: Maxine Everett "Max" COBURN and Beulah Pearl WARREN.William H. COBURN was born on 15 September 1860 in Avalon, Livingston, Missouri. He died on 14 October 1933 at the age of 73 in Chula, Livingston, Missouri. He was buried on 18 October 1933 in Burnside Cemetery, Livingston, Missouri. Parents: Luther COBURN and Elizabeth "Betty" PATTERSON.

Spouse: Sarah Jane APPLEBERRY. Sarah Jane APPLEBERRY and William H. COBURN were married on 15 September 1891 in Carroll Co., Missouri. Children were: Florence Belle COBURN, Homer COBURN, Jewell Linnius COBURN, Glen COBURN, Wilma COBURN.

William H. COBURN was born about 1928 in Missouri. Parents: Homer COBURN and Ina Felicia GARR.William Henry COBURN was born on 5 April 1925 in Livingston Co., Missouri. He died on 7 September 1925 at the age of 0 in Rich Hill Twp., Livingston, Missouri. He was buried on 9 September 1925 in Plainview Cemetery, Livingston, Missouri. Parents: Jewell Linnius COBURN and Gertrude Ethyl SCOVILLE.Wilma COBURN was born on 1 January 1911 in Missouri. She died on 23 August 1986 at the age of 75 in Auburn, DeKalb, Indiana. She was buried in Marion, Grant, Indiana. Parents: William H. COBURN and Sarah Jane APPLEBERRY.

Spouse: Clarence Alfred JEFFRIES. Wilma COBURN and Clarence Alfred JEFFRIES were married.

COCHENOUR was born (date unknown).

Spouse: Wanda Ann BARLOW. Wanda Ann BARLOW and COCHENOUR were married. Children were: Travis COCHENOUR.

Bernice Reva COCHENOUR was born on 18 October 1935 in Mandeville, Carroll, Missouri. She died on 19 March 2005 at the age of 69 in North Kansas City Hospital, Clay, Missouri. Her residence was in Bosworth, Missouri. She was buried on 23 March 2005 in Wharton Cemetery, Carroll, Missouri. Parents: Floyd Lester COCHENOUR and Amy Reba BROWNLEY.

Spouse: Jack Eldon HANAVAN. Bernice Reva COCHENOUR and Jack Eldon HANAVAN were married on 23 December 1952 in Mendon, Chariton, Missouri. Children were: Jerry HANAVAN, Terry HANAVAN.

Delores Fern COCHENOUR was born about 1938 in Missouri. Parents: Floyd Lester COCHENOUR and Amy Reba BROWNLEY.

Spouse: Jerry O'NEAL. Delores Fern COCHENOUR and Jerry O'NEAL were married.

Floyd Lester COCHENOUR was born on 5 November 1910 in Missouri. He died on 10 November 1984 at the age of 74. He was buried in Enon Cemetery, Carroll, Missouri. A retired farmer, he was caretaker of Edgewood Cemetery from 1974 to 1981. Parents: George COCHENOUR and Caroline LONGBRAKE.

Spouse: Amy Reba BROWNLEY. Amy Reba BROWNLEY and Floyd Lester COCHENOUR were married on 9 October 1930 in Chillicothe, Livingston, Missouri. The bride was of Dawn, the groom of Carrollton. George A. and Callie Cochenour, parents of Floyd, give consent. C. M. and Dora Brownley, parents of Amy, give consent. Children were: Francis Dale COCHENOUR, Kenneth Ray COCHENOUR, Bernice Reva COCHENOUR, Delores Fern COCHENOUR, James Hadley COCHENOUR.

Spouse: Irma Eileen COLDIRON. Irma Eileen COLDIRON and Floyd Lester COCHENOUR were married on 6 August 1982.

Francis Dale COCHENOUR was born about 1931 in Missouri. Parents: Floyd Lester COCHENOUR and Amy Reba BROWNLEY.George COCHENOUR was born (date unknown).

Spouse: Caroline LONGBRAKE. Caroline LONGBRAKE and George COCHENOUR were married. Children were: Floyd Lester COCHENOUR.

James Hadley COCHENOUR was born (date unknown). Parents: Floyd Lester COCHENOUR and Amy Reba BROWNLEY.

Spouse: Deborah Sue ROSS. Deborah Sue ROSS and James Hadley COCHENOUR were married on 6 June 1965 in Hale, Carroll, Missouri. Bride and groom were of Hale. The unnamed mother of Deborah Sue gives consent.

Jim COCHENOUR was born (date unknown).

Spouse: Debera ROSS. Debera ROSS and Jim COCHENOUR were married.

Kenneth COCHENOUR was born (date unknown).

Spouse: Janice CLEMENTS. Janice CLEMENTS and Kenneth COCHENOUR were married.

Kenneth Ray COCHENOUR was born on 2 February 1933 in Mandeville, Carroll, Missouri. He died on 25 March 1985 at the age of 52 in Kansas City, Jackson, Missouri. He was buried in Fairland Cemetery, Carroll, Missouri. Parents: Floyd Lester COCHENOUR and Amy Reba BROWNLEY.

Spouse: Janice Sue CLEMENTS. Janice Sue CLEMENTS and Kenneth Ray COCHENOUR were married on 26 October 1955 in Hale, Carroll, Missouri.

Travis COCHENOUR was born (date unknown). Parents: COCHENOUR and Wanda Ann BARLOW.Helen COCHLIN was born on 29 November 1904 in Missouri. She died on 11 July 1976 at the age of 71. She was buried in Masonic Cemetery, Jamesport, Missouri.

Spouse: Herbert TRIMBLE. Helen COCHLIN and Herbert TRIMBLE were married on 26 November 1935.

Allen Thurman COCHRAN was born about 1861 in Columbus, Franklin, Ohio.

Spouse: Elizabeth Audie KIRKPATRICK. Elizabeth Audie KIRKPATRICK and Allen Thurman COCHRAN were married. Children were: Mabel Izora COCHRAN.

Asa COCHRAN was born (date unknown).

Spouse: Esther CURTIS. Esther CURTIS and Asa COCHRAN were married.

Charles Vernon COCHRAN was born on 24 July 1891 in Shawnee Co., Kansas. He died on 6 June 1985 at the age of 93 in Chillicothe, Livingston, Missouri. He was buried in Topeka, Shawnee, Kansas. Burial was in Prairie Home Cemetery, Topeka, Kansas. Parents: Joseph Wills COCHRAN and Eva GODWIN.

Spouse: Faith HAMAKER. Faith HAMAKER and Charles Vernon COCHRAN were married on 21 February 1917. Children were: Ruth Elizabeth COCHRAN, Dr. George COCHRAN, Dorothy COCHRAN, Ethel COCHRAN.

Dorothy COCHRAN was born (date unknown). Parents: Charles Vernon COCHRAN and Faith HAMAKER.Elizabeth COCHRAN was born (date unknown).

Spouse: William CARAWAY. Elizabeth COCHRAN and William CARAWAY were married. Children were: Thomas CARAWAY.

Elizabeth COCHRAN was born on 31 January 1835 in New York, New York, New York. She died on 26 September 1921 at the age of 86 in Nodaway Co., Missouri. She was buried on 27 September 1921 in Mt. Moriah, Harrison, Missouri. Parents: John McRae COCHRANE and Agnes Forrest CURRIE.

Spouse: John R. "Jake" CHAMBERS. Elizabeth COCHRAN and John R. "Jake" CHAMBERS were married on 10 April 1862 in Cainsville, Harrison, Missouri. Children were: Isaiah Robert CHAMBERS, James Alexander CHAMBERS, John W. CHAMBERS, Minnie A. CHAMBERS.

Elsie COCHRAN was born (date unknown). Parents: Joseph Wills COCHRAN and Eva GODWIN.Ethel COCHRAN was born (date unknown). Parents: Charles Vernon COCHRAN and Faith HAMAKER.Dr. George COCHRAN was born about 1919. He died on 10 August 1984 at the age of 65 in Topeka, Shawnee, Kansas. He was buried in Topeka, Shawnee, Kansas. Parents: Charles Vernon COCHRAN and Faith HAMAKER.

Spouse: unknown . Unknown and Dr. George COCHRAN were married. Children were: Patricia COCHRAN, Lois COCHRAN.

Hulda COCHRAN was born in 1806 in Fauqier Co., Virginia. She died on 2 October 1892 at the age of 86 in Vigo Co., Indiana. She was buried in Farmersburg, Sullivan, Indiana.

Spouse: Alford HAMPTON. Hulda COCHRAN and Alford HAMPTON were married. Children were: Robert Francis HAMPTON.

Jerome Lee COCHRAN was born in December 1868 in Chillicothe, Livingston, Missouri. He died on 16 March 1923 at the age of 54 in Reno, Washoe, Nevada. He was buried in Reno, Washoe, Nevada. Parents: John Thomas COCHRAN Sr. and Mary GIBBS.John Edwin COCHRAN was born on 10 September 1899 in Breckenridge, Caldwell, Missouri. Parents: John Thomas COCHRAN Jr. and Minnie M. NEFF.John Thomas COCHRAN Sr. was born on 18 February 1836 in Ohio. He died on 2 May 1897 at the age of 61 in Chillicothe, Livingston, Missouri. He was buried in Edgewood Cemetery, Livingston, Missouri.

Spouse: Mary GIBBS. Mary GIBBS and John Thomas COCHRAN Sr. were married. Children were: Sarah M. "Sallie" COCHRAN, John Thomas COCHRAN Jr., Jerome Lee COCHRAN.

John Thomas COCHRAN Jr. was born on 9 March 1864 in Chillicothe, Livingston, Missouri. He died on 11 July 1936 at the age of 72 in Kansas City, Jackson, Missouri. He died in a Kansas City hospital; his usual residence was in Breckenridge. He was buried on 13 July 1936 in Rose Hill Cemetery, Caldwell, Missouri. He was employed as a tinner. Parents: John Thomas COCHRAN Sr. and Mary GIBBS.

Spouse: Minnie M. NEFF. Minnie M. NEFF and John Thomas COCHRAN Jr. were married on 7 April 1897 in Breckenridge, Caldwell, Missouri. Children were: John Edwin COCHRAN, Robert L. COCHRAN, Mary Isabell COCHRAN.

Joseph Wills COCHRAN was born (date unknown).

Spouse: Eva GODWIN. Eva GODWIN and Joseph Wills COCHRAN were married. Children were: Charles Vernon COCHRAN, Elsie COCHRAN, Lola COCHRAN.

Leila COCHRAN was born about 1899 in Illinois. Parents: Oliver COCHRAN and Edith A. MARSH.Lela Mae COCHRAN was born (date unknown).

Spouse: James Edgar ELSE. Lela Mae COCHRAN and James Edgar ELSE were married on 4 April 1917 in Chillicothe, Livingston, Missouri. The bride was of Carroll Co., the groom of Caldwell Co.

Lelia Dell COCHRAN was born (date unknown).

Spouse: Dr. Isaac Marion WOODEN. Lelia Dell COCHRAN and Dr. Isaac Marion WOODEN were married on 19 October 1913 in Carroll Co., Missouri.
